<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3780:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-13T20:00:00-03:00">June 13, 1940—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 13—1:57 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>275. My 272, June 11, midnight [<hi rend="italic">June 12, 8 p.m.</hi>].
                            The President issued late this afternoon through the Department of Press
                            and Propaganda the statement mentioned which the press associations will
                            carry. He assures me his sentiments have not changed and he is still
                            prepared to cooperate 100 percent with us.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>